graph
Interface Graph

public interface Graph

Interface for traversing a state graph on-the-fly. Note that graph objects do not contain a full explicit state graph; they only contain an implicit description of the graph, which is used to generate successor states on request. Objects implementing this interface are not expected to be thread-safe.

Method Summary

          Returns the initial state of the graph.

post

List<State> post(State state)
Returns all the successor states of state. States are generated using an implicit description of the state graph.

Parameters:
state - The state for which the list of successor states should be generated.
Returns:
A new list containing the successor states of state.
